<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="top_menu_widgets"><a class="link" href="#top_menu_widgets">Top menu widgets</a></h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><span class="image"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" width="64" height="20" role="img" aria-label="CS: 4.1.0"><title>CS: 4.1.0</title><linearGradient id="s" x2="0" y2="100%"><stop offset="0" stop-color="#bbb" stop-opacity=".1"/><stop offset="1" stop-opacity=".1"/></linearGradient><clipPath id="r"><rect width="64" height="20" rx="3" fill="#fff"/></clipPath><g clip-path="url(#r)"><rect width="25" height="20" fill="#555"/><rect x="25" width="39" height="20" fill="#007ec6"/><rect width="64" height="20" fill="url(#s)"/></g><g fill="#fff" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Verdana,Geneva,DejaVu Sans,sans-serif" text-rendering="geometricPrecision" font-size="110"><text aria-hidden="true" x="135" y="150" fill="#010101" fill-opacity=".3" transform="scale(.1)" textLength="150">CS</text><text x="135" y="140" transform="scale(.1)" fill="#fff" textLength="150">CS</text><text aria-hidden="true" x="435" y="150" fill="#010101" fill-opacity=".3" transform="scale(.1)" textLength="290">4.1.0</text><text x="435" y="140" transform="scale(.1)" fill="#fff" textLength="290">4.1.0</text></g></svg></span></p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Widgets with interface <code>contentstudio.menuitem</code> will expand the left-hand side menu of Content Studio. They are so-called "fullscreen widgets" which will take up the entire screen
between the Content Studio header and the left-side menu. Widget icon will be automatically injected inside the sidebar menu when you deploy an application containing your widget.</p>
</div>
<div class="listingblock">
<div class="title">Sample XML for a widget with <code>contentstudio.menuitem</code> interface:</div>
<div class="content">
<pre class="highlight"><code class="language-xml" data-lang="xml">&lt;widget&gt;
  &lt;display-name&gt;My widget&lt;/display-name&gt;
  &lt;description&gt;This widget is for the Content Studio menu&lt;/description&gt;
  &lt;interfaces&gt;
    &lt;interface&gt;contentstudio.menuitem&lt;/interface&gt;
  &lt;/interfaces&gt;
  &lt;config&gt;
    &lt;property name="context" value="project"/&gt;
  &lt;/config&gt;
&lt;/widget&gt;</code></pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class="imageblock">
<div class="content">
<img src="widgets/images/widgets-menu-item.png" alt="widgets menu item" width="600">
</div>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
By specifying optional config as shown in the example above, you let Content Studio know that your widget is project-dependent and requires project selector in the header.
</td>
</tr>
</table>
